♪ We're girls girls
Girls girls ♪

03:10.494 --> 03:13.062
♪ And we like
Boys boys boys boys ♪

03:13.105 --> 03:14.498
-[switches off radio]
-♪ Girls girls--

03:14.542 --> 03:17.936
What! I missed you!
Can't I miss you?

03:19.242 --> 03:20.287
Yeah, I missed you, too.

03:20.330 --> 03:22.767
Great! So then next year
you stay home!

03:23.986 --> 03:25.640
-Maybe.
-Oh, come on, baby girl,

03:25.683 --> 03:27.903
don't you think you're getting
a little old for that camp?

03:29.121 --> 03:30.949
-If it's cause of Tommy--
-It's not.

03:30.993 --> 03:31.994
[Michelle] Well, if it is--

03:32.037 --> 03:33.387
-It's not!
-I'm just saying,

03:33.430 --> 03:36.041
it wouldn't kill you
to maybe dress a bit sexier

03:36.085 --> 03:37.304
-every now and then.
-Okay, look, Mom!

03:37.347 --> 03:40.176
Tommy is cute,
but he's not why I go there.

03:40.220 --> 03:42.526
You know that.
So, please stop.

03:42.570 --> 03:43.962
-Fine.
-Please.

03:44.006 --> 03:45.442
Fine. Fine.

03:57.237 --> 03:58.238
Can you scratch my arm?

04:02.764 --> 04:03.721
Hm-mm.

04:03.765 --> 04:06.681
[suspenseful music]

04:13.165 --> 04:16.560
[suspenseful music continues]

04:26.309 --> 04:29.051
[deep sigh]
You wanna drive?

04:29.094 --> 04:30.357
You? Really?

04:30.400 --> 04:31.532
Sure!

04:31.575 --> 04:33.534
Don't I need like a permit?

04:33.577 --> 04:34.883
Do you want to drive or not?

04:36.232 --> 04:38.408
[car door opens]

04:43.805 --> 04:46.198
-[car door closes]
-Oh, look at you! All excited!

04:46.242 --> 04:48.505
Yaaaay! [chuckles]Yes! Seatbelt.

04:48.549 --> 04:50.507
-[seatbelt locks]
-[Michelle] Check, okay.

04:50.551 --> 04:53.858
Hands at ten-two,foot on the brake

04:53.902 --> 04:55.643
and put the car into drive.

04:55.686 --> 04:57.340
But che-checkyour blind spot first.

04:57.384 --> 04:58.646
And-and the mirror.

04:58.689 --> 05:00.212
Oh, God!You'll have to adjust those.

05:00.256 --> 05:02.998
And the seat--God, is it getting hot in here?

05:03.041 --> 05:04.521
Wait!But, don't forget to signal!

05:04.565 --> 05:05.914
Mom!

05:05.957 --> 05:07.219
Too much?

05:07.263 --> 05:08.264
Okay.

05:16.794 --> 05:20.798
Oh! Look at you. [sighs]

05:20.842 --> 05:23.888
Ah! [laughs]

05:23.932 --> 05:26.064
You're doing great.

05:26.108 --> 05:28.415
Okay, steady.

05:28.458 --> 05:32.462
You show, hey-- Libby, Libby,Libby, road! [breathes deeply]

05:32.506 --> 05:34.421
-Mom!
-What?

05:36.205 --> 05:37.859
It's just for
one of the vacant lots.

05:37.902 --> 05:39.643
We talked about this!

05:39.687 --> 05:41.819
Oh.

05:41.863 --> 05:44.387
We're gonna need moneyfor college, baby girl.

05:44.431 --> 05:47.477
The romance stories aren'tselling like they used to.

05:47.521 --> 05:49.000
I know.

05:49.044 --> 05:50.741
Betty said she's stillwilling to show us

05:50.785 --> 05:52.047
around at SUNY Adirondack.

05:53.875 --> 05:55.311
SUNY.

05:55.355 --> 05:56.921
[Michelle]What? It's affordable.

05:56.965 --> 05:59.359
[chuckles]
Yeah, affordable, huh?

05:59.402 --> 06:01.535
What? Don't you dare!It was a gift!

06:01.578 --> 06:02.884
-Gi--gift?
-Yeah.

06:02.927 --> 06:03.928
From who?

06:03.972 --> 06:07.541
[sighs] Mm-mm.You'll see

06:13.677 --> 06:16.114
-Um, whose--?
-Great job, baby girl!!!

06:16.158 --> 06:18.465
-[car door opens]
-[Michelle] Come on.

06:18.508 --> 06:19.509
[car door slams]

06:21.206 --> 06:22.251
[Michelle] We're here!

06:22.294 --> 06:23.426
[car door slams]

06:24.775 --> 06:26.951
Babe?

06:26.995 --> 06:28.257
[heavy footsteps]

06:28.300 --> 06:29.345
Babe?

06:29.389 --> 06:30.346
Mom?

06:30.390 --> 06:31.695
Hello?

06:31.739 --> 06:33.175
-What are you--?
-[John] Hey!

06:39.355 --> 06:41.444
[Libby breathes deeply]

06:46.144 --> 06:47.363
Holy crap.

06:55.153 --> 06:56.981
[Michelle] I know.

06:57.025 --> 06:58.809
I'm writing him constantly.

07:00.245 --> 07:01.769
Eww.

07:01.812 --> 07:02.813
[Michelle] Hm-mm.

07:09.864 --> 07:11.256
Who wears a speedo?

07:13.955 --> 07:19.177
Libs, this is
my boyfriend, John.

07:19.221 --> 07:21.484
Miss Wells,[breathes deeply]

07:21.528 --> 07:23.094
it's a pleasure
to finally meet you!

07:25.314 --> 07:27.185
Libby? [giggles]

07:27.229 --> 07:28.230
Hey.

07:29.840 --> 07:32.408
I hope you don't mind
that I'm here!

07:32.452 --> 07:33.801
I know it's your Lake house

07:33.844 --> 07:36.543
and I'm not trying totake away time with your Mom.

07:36.586 --> 07:38.632
So--

07:38.675 --> 07:40.721
Oh! I've actually
got something for you.

07:40.764 --> 07:41.939
Can you give me just a minute?

07:46.422 --> 07:48.163
You have a boyfriend?

07:48.206 --> 07:49.381
I know!

07:50.557 --> 07:51.732
Why didn't you tell me?

07:51.775 --> 07:53.734
[scoffs]I thought it was just a fling!

07:53.777 --> 07:56.040
I mean, look at him.

07:56.084 --> 07:58.565
Is he what you were "doing"
every time I called?

07:59.827 --> 08:01.959
Okay.

08:02.003 --> 08:03.526
This is for you.

08:09.532 --> 08:11.142
Your mom told me

08:11.186 --> 08:12.883
that you're really
into archeology.

08:14.537 --> 08:21.109
This is the Navajo tribes'"stone of life".

08:21.152 --> 08:23.764
It's the only "object"they really assign any value to

08:23.807 --> 08:26.418
outside of its utility.

08:26.462 --> 08:29.117
And, if you look here,

08:29.160 --> 08:31.859
the upside-downcrescent moon shape?

08:31.902 --> 08:34.557
It's called a 'Naja'
by the Navajo,

08:34.601 --> 08:39.780
but [chuckles] it's actuallyMoorish in origin!

08:39.823 --> 08:46.569
It represents the Phoeniciangoddess of fertility.

08:46.613 --> 08:49.529
Basically,this bracelet has origins

08:49.572 --> 08:53.271
from the Western
and Eastern world

08:53.315 --> 08:56.187
all the way back to the verybeginning of civilization.

08:57.667 --> 08:58.668
So--

09:00.931 --> 09:02.759
Thanks.

09:02.803 --> 09:04.065
You're very welcome.

09:05.588 --> 09:07.938
Oh, if you want

09:10.593 --> 09:12.856
the gift receipt,
it's in the box.

09:16.904 --> 09:19.036
Well, who's hungry?

09:40.667 --> 09:42.059
[bangles clink]

09:45.106 --> 09:47.456
[Libby breathing rapidly]

09:59.468 --> 10:01.209
Hey

10:01.252 --> 10:05.082
[breathes deeply]
Yeah. Don't be a weirdo.

10:05.126 --> 10:07.171
[breathes deeply] Please.

10:07.215 --> 10:09.043
[John] Honey, dessert. What am Igonna have for dessert?

10:09.086 --> 10:10.653
[Michelle laughing]

10:10.697 --> 10:13.830
[laughs] Hey!

10:13.874 --> 10:14.875
Hi.

10:20.141 --> 10:21.577
Hope you're hungry, baby girl!

10:27.496 --> 10:28.628
You look nice.

10:31.282 --> 10:32.240
You cooked?

10:32.283 --> 10:33.241
Of course, I cooked!

10:33.284 --> 10:36.331
Eh-eh-eh I'll get that.

10:36.374 --> 10:37.462
-Oh, yeah?
-[John chuckles]

10:37.506 --> 10:39.203
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

10:39.247 --> 10:40.509
Mm-mm.

10:40.552 --> 10:42.859
Oh, that tastes really good.

10:42.903 --> 10:45.906
Mm-mm. [laughs]

10:45.949 --> 10:49.605
[John] So, Libby?
How was camp?

10:49.649 --> 10:50.867
Uh. It was okay.

10:50.911 --> 10:52.521
-[John] Yeah?
-Yeah.

10:52.564 --> 10:55.002
I think it's getting like,uh, a little routine.

10:57.526 --> 10:59.310
How did you guys meet?

10:59.354 --> 11:00.921
[Michelle breathes deeply]

11:00.964 --> 11:02.531
I will let you
take that one.

11:02.574 --> 11:06.709
Well, uh, I-I came out
early this year

11:06.753 --> 11:10.495
because some work needed
to be done to the back deck.

11:10.539 --> 11:11.671
I swear!

11:13.020 --> 11:17.067
Anyways, I was outside
writing on the porch one day

11:17.111 --> 11:20.897
when John just
kind of appeared!

11:20.941 --> 11:24.727
[laughs] I--I've been
at the Lake all year.

11:24.771 --> 11:27.643
I, uh, I'm studying
a few species here.

11:27.687 --> 11:29.514
He's an aquatic geneticist!

11:29.558 --> 11:31.516
-Wait, really?
-[John] Hm-mm. Yeah.

11:31.560 --> 11:33.388
I'm part of
a small research team.

11:33.431 --> 11:35.651
We're sort of scattered
around the region here.

11:35.695 --> 11:37.261
What are you researching?

11:37.305 --> 11:39.089
[John]
Mostly freshwater animals.

11:39.133 --> 11:41.135
We're trying to solve
a problem in nature.

11:41.178 --> 11:43.485
Hm-mm. Libs! [indistinct].

11:43.528 --> 11:45.008
What problem?

11:45.052 --> 11:46.053
Well

11:49.186 --> 11:51.319
Can I borrow this, please?

11:51.362 --> 11:53.887
-Of course.
-[John chuckles]

11:53.930 --> 11:56.541
So the earth hasa finite amount of freshwater.

11:56.585 --> 11:57.934
[water gurgles]

11:57.978 --> 12:04.027
In fact, only 2.5%
of the Earth's water is fresh,

12:04.071 --> 12:06.464
leaving 97.5%

12:06.508 --> 12:09.641
-[clanking]
-as salt water.

12:09.685 --> 12:14.646
And within those freshwater
ponds and streams,

12:14.690 --> 12:17.737
and glaciers,
many, many species live.

12:17.780 --> 12:21.044
Unfortunately,
due to continual increase

12:21.088 --> 12:22.567
in the Earth's temperature,

12:22.611 --> 12:26.528
there isn't enough rain tosupply these freshwater systems.

12:26.571 --> 12:32.969
And there's more evaporation
in the oceans leaving a planet

12:33.013 --> 12:34.536
[clanking]

12:34.579 --> 12:36.494
with an overall
increasing level

12:36.538 --> 12:38.583
[clanking]

12:38.627 --> 12:39.628
of salinity.

12:40.934 --> 12:44.938
And now,
some of the species,

12:44.981 --> 12:49.812
well, they can't survivein such a rapidly changing world

12:49.856 --> 12:53.816
without some major adaptation.

12:53.860 --> 13:01.868
So, I am here
to speed up Mother Nature.

13:03.913 --> 13:05.262
And

13:07.961 --> 13:10.137
hopefully

13:10.180 --> 13:11.616
in the end

13:11.660 --> 13:14.576
[water flowing]

13:14.619 --> 13:18.754
make it
so that certain species

13:18.798 --> 13:22.105
can survive
in a saltwater world.

13:23.715 --> 13:26.327
[Michelle breathes deeply]

13:29.678 --> 13:33.290
Hm-mm. So, basically,
he's saving the world.

13:33.334 --> 13:34.422
[John] Oh, come on.

13:34.465 --> 13:36.293
I'm definitely not. [laughs]

13:36.337 --> 13:37.686
[Michelle laughs]

13:42.299 --> 13:44.301
[John clears throat and coughs]

13:45.650 --> 13:48.436
-Hon?
-[John coughs intensely]

13:58.228 --> 13:59.621
[John] Oh, man.

13:59.664 --> 14:01.405
Sorry. [coughs]

14:01.449 --> 14:03.625
Ah, I coughed up
a lung there.

14:03.668 --> 14:04.974
You know that phrase.

14:05.018 --> 14:07.107
-It's actually, well--
-Honey, honey.

14:07.150 --> 14:09.326
[exhales] Mm.

14:15.028 --> 14:16.377
[Libby gasps]

14:42.620 --> 14:45.188
[Libby moans]

14:53.762 --> 14:56.808
[Libby breathes deeply]

14:58.158 --> 14:59.376
[clank]

15:01.857 --> 15:03.250
[in-can drink fizzes]

15:16.524 --> 15:17.742
[Michelle] [moans] Ah!

15:22.530 --> 15:23.923
[moaning] Aaaah!

15:23.966 --> 15:26.795
[continues moaning
and breathing rapidly]

15:37.240 --> 15:39.025
[floorboards creak]

15:49.949 --> 15:53.343
[continues moaning
and breathing rapidly]

16:05.007 --> 16:06.748
[bang]

16:06.791 --> 16:08.271
[door hinges squeak]

16:19.674 --> 16:22.938
[water flowing]

16:25.375 --> 16:27.943
[heavy footsteps]

16:49.791 --> 16:54.143
[tense music]

16:58.060 --> 17:00.410
[door hinges squeak]

17:04.327 --> 17:05.850
[door closes]

17:11.073 --> 17:12.988
[Libby breathes deeply]

17:13.032 --> 17:16.035
[birds chirping]

17:16.078 --> 17:18.254
-[banging]
-[Libby breathes deeply]

17:20.996 --> 17:22.258
[Michelle giggles and inhales]

17:22.302 --> 17:23.999
[John] Oh, I like things
that are kind of wet.

17:24.043 --> 17:25.044
-Oh, yeah.
-[John] Hm-mm.

17:25.087 --> 17:26.436
You're evil. [laughs]

17:26.480 --> 17:27.611
[indistinct]. What?

17:27.655 --> 17:29.135
[Michelle]
[giggles] No, I didn't.

17:29.178 --> 17:30.136
[John chuckles]

17:30.179 --> 17:33.487
[giggles] Mm.
Scratch my arm.

17:33.530 --> 17:34.531
Hm...mm.

17:38.492 --> 17:40.146
Mm-hm.

17:40.189 --> 17:43.149
-[far counter bangs]
-Oh. [shocked]

17:43.192 --> 17:44.454
Morning, sunshine!

17:44.498 --> 17:46.108
Morning.

17:46.152 --> 17:48.110
How'd you sleep?

17:48.154 --> 17:50.025
Well, thanks.

17:50.069 --> 17:51.418
You want some breakfast?

17:51.461 --> 17:54.464
I was thinking we could
go for a hike later?

17:54.508 --> 17:55.596
[chuckles] Mom?

17:55.639 --> 17:57.076
[Michelle] What?

17:57.119 --> 17:58.686
It's the 28th.

17:58.729 --> 18:00.209
Okay

18:00.253 --> 18:01.645
August 28th!

18:03.691 --> 18:06.650
Oh. [chuckles]
We can go after breakfast.

18:11.438 --> 18:12.482
Can John come?

18:14.093 --> 18:17.705
Ahhh I-I don't know.

18:17.748 --> 18:19.968
Okay, fine. Just us two.

18:20.011 --> 18:22.884
[breathes deeply]
I'll explain later. Hm.

18:22.927 --> 18:24.277
-It's fine.
-[both kiss]

18:24.320 --> 18:26.061
[Michelle] I'm gonna
make you some breakfast.

18:26.105 --> 18:28.368
-[both kiss]
-You'll love it.

18:28.411 --> 18:30.326
[heavy footsteps]

18:35.114 --> 18:37.377
[birds chirping]

18:40.206 --> 18:41.685
So, what do you think
of John?

18:43.644 --> 18:45.080
Mom.

18:45.124 --> 18:46.473
Ugh.

18:46.516 --> 18:48.692
It's important to me
that you like him.

18:51.826 --> 18:53.828
[sighs deeply]

18:53.871 --> 18:56.135
[capsules clanking]

19:17.330 --> 19:18.853
I don't have
anything this year.

19:21.464 --> 19:22.465
Fine.

19:23.945 --> 19:24.946
What about Grandpa?

19:26.774 --> 19:27.862
Mom!

19:27.905 --> 19:29.733
It's been nine years, Libs!

19:29.777 --> 19:30.952
So?

19:30.995 --> 19:32.562
Alright. I'm gonna
go back to the house.

19:32.606 --> 19:35.348
Fine. You never gave a shit,anyways so--

19:37.480 --> 19:38.525
Hey!

19:38.568 --> 19:40.048
Hey, what?

19:40.091 --> 19:42.355
You never haveanything nice for him.

19:42.398 --> 19:44.226
And one year, you gave hima roll of toilet paper!

19:44.270 --> 19:47.925
[laughs] That was funny!
He was gassy!

19:47.969 --> 19:49.536
Just go play
with your boyfriend.

19:54.062 --> 19:56.543
Hm. I think I will.

19:56.586 --> 19:58.109
No wonder
he gave me the house.

19:59.546 --> 20:00.851
Excuse me?

20:02.984 --> 20:06.030
He gave you the house
because he loved you!

20:06.074 --> 20:09.295
He loved you, Libby,
more than he ever loved me.

20:09.338 --> 20:10.339
Yeah.That's kind of my point.

20:10.383 --> 20:12.036
No. No, Libby.
You don't get it.

20:12.080 --> 20:14.082
He <i>never</i>loved me.

20:14.125 --> 20:17.868
You wanna know why I don't
give him a note every year?

20:17.912 --> 20:19.000
You want to know why?

20:20.175 --> 20:21.872
Because after he died,

20:21.916 --> 20:24.179
and I was cleaning out
this shithole house,

20:24.223 --> 20:27.269
I found his divorce
agreement to Grandma.

20:27.313 --> 20:29.184
He wrote to the lawyers
saying,

20:29.228 --> 20:32.318
"She can have Michelle,
I'll take Marc."

20:34.494 --> 20:35.495
That.

20:36.931 --> 20:38.237
That was the last note.

20:39.412 --> 20:41.240
That was the only note.

20:41.283 --> 20:44.199
[heavy footsteps]

20:51.424 --> 20:54.514
[insects chirping]

21:11.531 --> 21:12.880
[gasps] Ow!

21:14.447 --> 21:15.926
Ow! [groans softly]

21:15.970 --> 21:18.320
[breathing deeply]

21:18.364 --> 21:19.800
[John] No. Stop! Stop! Stop!

21:21.367 --> 21:22.803
That's a Scolopendra!

21:23.978 --> 21:25.588
They're really rare!

21:25.632 --> 21:26.850
[gasps]

21:31.290 --> 21:32.378
Careful.

21:34.118 --> 21:35.337
Let's get back in there.

21:35.381 --> 21:37.426
Alright, come on.

21:37.470 --> 21:38.775
It bit me!

21:40.386 --> 21:44.912
Well, I would guess, ah

21:47.175 --> 21:49.220
It was protecting its offspring.

21:51.919 --> 21:53.050
There we--

21:53.094 --> 21:54.835
Sorry, I didn't know
it was doing that.

21:56.489 --> 21:58.273
That's all right.

21:58.317 --> 22:00.014
[Libby breathes deeply]

22:01.624 --> 22:03.844
[John breathes deeply]

22:03.887 --> 22:05.236
Where did she get you?

22:06.412 --> 22:07.413
Right here.

22:07.456 --> 22:08.675
[John] Let me see.

22:11.286 --> 22:12.374
Whoa!I don't want to scare you,

22:12.418 --> 22:14.071
but their bite is venomous.

22:31.959 --> 22:33.656
Looks like
you're gonna be okay.

22:35.702 --> 22:38.618
Just put some ice on itso it doesn't swell, okay?

22:38.661 --> 22:39.706
Okay.

22:43.710 --> 22:45.581
What were you doing out here?

22:45.625 --> 22:48.279
Um, I like to come out here
after it rains.

22:49.585 --> 22:52.240
See if anything gets unearthed.

22:52.283 --> 22:54.329
[water splashing]

22:55.896 --> 22:57.158
You?

22:59.465 --> 23:01.162
Came to check on you, actually.

23:02.859 --> 23:04.078
Oh.

23:05.471 --> 23:06.733
Everything okay?

23:08.256 --> 23:10.040
Yeah. Fine.

23:10.084 --> 23:11.433
Hm-mm.

23:14.044 --> 23:16.395
I know it's not really
my business, but, uh

23:18.353 --> 23:20.007
your Mom came back
pretty upset.

23:23.750 --> 23:24.881
Oh.

23:28.668 --> 23:32.280
I hope it's nothing
with me being here.

23:35.588 --> 23:37.894
Maybe I should take off.

23:37.938 --> 23:39.461
Our team's almost done
around here.

23:39.505 --> 23:41.420
I can finish up at home.

23:42.551 --> 23:44.205
I don't want to cause
a rift between you two.

23:45.859 --> 23:48.035
I know how much
she loves you.

23:48.078 --> 23:51.821
[chuckles] You know,
the way she described you,

23:51.865 --> 23:53.475
the way she talked
about you

23:55.912 --> 23:57.740
it's what made me
fall in love with her.

24:05.008 --> 24:06.183
You love her?

24:08.621 --> 24:09.883
Very, very much.

24:13.103 --> 24:15.279
Well, I'll be in the basement
packing up my stuff.

24:16.759 --> 24:19.893
Oh, I have some of my things
down there for the low light.

24:19.936 --> 24:21.851
Sorry, I should
I should have told you.

24:21.895 --> 24:23.157
It's okay.

24:25.681 --> 24:27.074
You know, you should stay.

24:30.904 --> 24:32.949
I'll go talk to her.

24:32.993 --> 24:36.692
[John] Ah, I would maybe
give her a little bit.

24:36.736 --> 24:38.955
Last I checked,
she wasn't feeling real great.

24:48.095 --> 24:50.053
[loud whisper] Mom?

24:50.097 --> 24:52.534
[door hinges squeak]

25:00.847 --> 25:02.022
Ma?

25:02.065 --> 25:03.371
Hm-mm.

25:09.725 --> 25:11.074
[Michelle]
I'm not drinking.

25:13.076 --> 25:15.252
I've been good this summer.
I swear.

25:15.296 --> 25:17.646
[deep sigh] Hm.

25:19.779 --> 25:21.258
Ah.

25:25.262 --> 25:27.874
[breathes deeply]

25:30.006 --> 25:31.138
What's wrong?

25:31.181 --> 25:32.922
[Michelle]Ah. My stomach.

25:34.184 --> 25:35.490
Must've been my cooking.

25:36.622 --> 25:37.927
[chuckles]

25:43.629 --> 25:46.370
I'm sorry, about before.

25:47.676 --> 25:49.678
I didn't know, so

25:49.722 --> 25:51.462
It's okay, baby girl.

25:53.203 --> 25:54.727
I'm sorry I told you.

25:56.685 --> 25:58.774
I know Pop-pop
meant a lot to you.

26:00.080 --> 26:01.516
This doesn't change that.

26:05.041 --> 26:07.261
Did you find anything cool?

26:07.304 --> 26:08.610
-Sort of.
-[Michelle] Hm.

26:09.742 --> 26:11.134
You should show John!

26:12.396 --> 26:14.268
I think you twohave a lot in common.

26:16.792 --> 26:19.752
[inhales deeply]

26:19.795 --> 26:21.710
Libs, there's somethingI got to tell you

26:21.754 --> 26:24.365
and I don't want youto freak out.

26:26.628 --> 26:27.716
Okay.

26:28.978 --> 26:30.110
Okay

26:30.153 --> 26:31.677
Ah, well

26:34.984 --> 26:39.075
John asked me to marry him,and I said "yes." [chuckles]

26:39.119 --> 26:40.816
Well, "hell, yes"to be exact.

26:40.860 --> 26:42.775
[chuckles]

26:42.818 --> 26:44.385
What?

26:44.428 --> 26:46.561
I love him, Libby.

26:46.605 --> 26:48.215
I love him so much.

26:48.258 --> 26:50.217
So, so much.

26:50.260 --> 26:52.306
He's amazing.

26:52.349 --> 26:53.481
And I know you'll love him too.

26:53.524 --> 26:55.091
I promise you will.

26:57.572 --> 26:59.879
It's important to me
that you're okay with this.

27:01.271 --> 27:03.447
I need you to be okay,baby girl. [exhales]

27:05.319 --> 27:06.799
Please don't call me that.

27:08.844 --> 27:10.237
Okay.

27:14.502 --> 27:15.895
I'm happy for you guys.

27:17.723 --> 27:18.854
I love you, Mom.

27:18.898 --> 27:19.942
I want you to be happy.

27:23.511 --> 27:26.645
Oh, I love you, baby--
I love you, Libs!

27:27.820 --> 27:29.256
Thank you,
thank you, thank you.

27:30.953 --> 27:33.564
[inhales deeply]
[chuckles]

27:35.392 --> 27:37.090
Just one more thing.

27:37.133 --> 27:38.787
Wh-what?

27:38.831 --> 27:41.921
John doesn't really know
that I'm 42.

27:41.964 --> 27:42.965
What do you mean?

27:44.575 --> 27:48.318
He thinks I'm 35?

27:48.362 --> 27:49.319
Mom! That so--

27:49.363 --> 27:50.712
[Michelle] I know,I know, I know!

27:50.756 --> 27:53.236
I'm-I'm gonna tell him.
I-I've been meaning to, just

27:56.283 --> 27:58.546
I-I can't lose him, Libs.

28:00.113 --> 28:02.289
I just, I can't.

28:02.332 --> 28:03.682
Hey, you won't.

28:05.248 --> 28:06.685
You're incredible, so

28:07.860 --> 28:09.644
[Michelle sighs]

28:10.645 --> 28:12.125
Hey

28:14.867 --> 28:16.129
I gotta-- I should

28:16.172 --> 28:18.914
I should clean up. Yeah.

28:18.958 --> 28:20.089
-Yeah.
-[Libby clears throat]

28:42.372 --> 28:43.939
[zipper screeching open]

29:23.109 --> 29:25.328
[Libby breathes deeply]

30:01.277 --> 30:03.366
[door hinges squeak]

30:17.293 --> 30:18.425
[John] Hello?

30:18.468 --> 30:20.035
[Libby] Ah. It's me.

30:20.079 --> 30:21.645
[John] Oh, hey!

30:21.689 --> 30:24.126
But, turn that light off, yeah,I'll-I'll come and get you.

30:31.917 --> 30:35.094
Hey, what an awesome surprise!

30:36.660 --> 30:38.662
I tried knocking.
I'm really sorry.

30:38.706 --> 30:40.055
Oh, it's okay.

30:40.099 --> 30:42.101
I'll be, uh, the humidifiers,they get really loud,

30:42.144 --> 30:45.147
so sometimes I don't hear.

30:45.191 --> 30:46.757
How's your Mom?

30:46.801 --> 30:49.412
[gasps] She's fine. Yeah.

30:49.456 --> 30:50.631
[John] Good.

30:50.674 --> 30:53.416
Um, I brought you
something to drink, so

30:53.460 --> 30:54.765
Thank you.

30:54.809 --> 30:58.595
Ah, I can't, uh,I can't do the sodium.

31:00.510 --> 31:03.905
Bad ticker.
But thank you.

31:03.949 --> 31:05.776
Hm-mm.
[whispers] Yeah.

31:05.820 --> 31:07.300
[John] So, uh

31:09.650 --> 31:11.826
you want to check out
my craziness?

31:18.528 --> 31:20.269
Right this way.Come here.

31:23.794 --> 31:25.753
[water gurgling]

31:28.016 --> 31:29.539
Uhh.

31:29.583 --> 31:31.628
What are those?

31:31.672 --> 31:34.022
[smirks] Lampreys.

31:34.066 --> 31:35.284
[Libby] Really?

31:35.328 --> 31:37.896
Yeah. You're familiar?

31:38.984 --> 31:40.072
Yeah. Slightly.

31:41.464 --> 31:42.770
I figured you might be.

31:44.119 --> 31:47.122
These little guys
are 360 million years old.

31:48.515 --> 31:50.169
Right up your alley!

31:50.212 --> 31:51.648
Ah, yeah. They're, um

31:51.692 --> 31:53.607
mentioned a lot
in the fossil record.

31:53.650 --> 31:54.695
Hm-mm.

31:56.001 --> 31:57.916
Yeah, these little guys
have survived it all.

31:59.482 --> 32:01.267
Meteors

32:01.310 --> 32:03.443
ice ages

32:03.486 --> 32:06.272
ever increasing and decreasing
salinity levels.

32:08.013 --> 32:11.625
In fact, they are
the only aquatic species

32:11.668 --> 32:15.020
to be found in the fresh
and saltwater records.

32:15.063 --> 32:16.412
Huh.

32:16.456 --> 32:18.284
They're parasitic.

32:18.327 --> 32:21.243
See the mouths? The teeth?

32:21.287 --> 32:23.985
They latch onto their prey.

32:24.029 --> 32:27.336
And they can adapt
to their host.

32:28.816 --> 32:32.515
So, even if they encounter
anadromous species

32:32.559 --> 32:37.085
like Smelt,
or Salmon, or Bass,

32:37.129 --> 32:38.869
spawning
in a freshwater pool,

32:38.913 --> 32:43.657
or stream, or river,
they can attach

32:43.700 --> 32:45.441
and then adapt.

32:45.485 --> 32:49.402
So even if they
end up in the sea

32:49.445 --> 32:50.577
they'll survive.

32:53.710 --> 32:56.017
No other species on Earth

32:56.061 --> 32:57.323
that can do that.

32:58.889 --> 33:00.152
Not one.

33:02.415 --> 33:04.852
[water bubbing]

33:12.207 --> 33:13.687
It's beautiful.

33:18.909 --> 33:20.085
Beautiful?

33:22.565 --> 33:24.480
Hm-mm. [chuckles]

33:26.178 --> 33:27.266
Yeah.

33:30.443 --> 33:32.053
You're kind of a-a weird dude.

33:32.097 --> 33:33.707
[John laughs]

33:35.796 --> 33:37.885
Yeah, I guess I am.

33:39.321 --> 33:40.583
But, I mean,

33:40.627 --> 33:42.020
weird is cool, right?

33:46.111 --> 33:47.373
Yeah.

33:52.465 --> 33:54.075
[Libby] Um

33:54.119 --> 33:56.773
So, I heard that you and
my mom are getting married?

34:00.603 --> 34:01.996
Yeah, yeah. Ah

34:05.434 --> 34:06.957
She told you, huh?

34:07.001 --> 34:08.916
Yep.

34:08.959 --> 34:10.439
Yeah, we are.

34:13.877 --> 34:16.271
Libby, she's very,
very special to me.

34:18.273 --> 34:19.622
Good.

34:21.189 --> 34:22.538
[John chuckles]

34:23.757 --> 34:25.759
We have to celebrate!

34:25.802 --> 34:27.152
You can have a party!

34:27.195 --> 34:28.588
You can invite
some of your girlfriends.

34:28.631 --> 34:29.676
Ah, I don't-- [chuckles]

34:29.719 --> 34:31.373
Maybe. [chuckles]

34:33.462 --> 34:35.029
Should I go check on your mom?
Or-or--

34:35.073 --> 34:37.379
Nah, no, no.
She's um, she's fine.

34:37.423 --> 34:39.468
Just let her sleep.

34:39.512 --> 34:41.122
[John] Okay.

34:41.166 --> 34:42.689
In that case

34:45.866 --> 34:48.129
you want to help me pull
some samples from the lake?

34:48.173 --> 34:50.131
[water bubbling]

34:51.915 --> 34:53.874
Oh, okay.

35:03.536 --> 35:04.972
How old are you?

35:06.626 --> 35:07.844
[John] How old do I look?

35:09.324 --> 35:10.282
[Libby] Twenty-five.

35:10.325 --> 35:12.501
Ho-oh, thank you.

35:12.545 --> 35:13.633
[Libby] Twenty-six?

35:14.938 --> 35:15.983
Thirty.

35:16.026 --> 35:17.245
Oh.

35:19.595 --> 35:21.293
Where did you go to school?

35:21.336 --> 35:25.253
Uh, a little, private school
that no one has ever heard of.

35:25.297 --> 35:27.777
It probably explainswhy I'm so well-funded.

35:27.821 --> 35:30.476
[boat groans]

35:32.347 --> 35:34.306
Can you hold my legs
for a second?

35:36.046 --> 35:37.135
Yep.

35:39.093 --> 35:40.050
[John] Right there.

35:40.094 --> 35:41.835
[water splashing]

35:41.878 --> 35:43.010
Come on.

35:45.143 --> 35:47.275
-Yeah.
-[cage thuds]

35:47.319 --> 35:49.625
Well, I'm applying
Early Decision

35:49.669 --> 35:51.149
to Cambridge next year.

35:52.411 --> 35:53.847
Really?

35:53.890 --> 35:55.805
[Libby] Yeah, I got, uh,
a perfect score on my PSATs

35:55.849 --> 35:57.590
and, um, my counselor says

35:57.633 --> 36:00.201
I'm probably gonna be
Valedictorian, so

36:00.245 --> 36:02.203
Libby, that's amazing!

36:02.247 --> 36:03.204
Thanks. [chuckles]

36:03.248 --> 36:04.684
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

36:04.727 --> 36:05.815
That's great.

36:05.859 --> 36:08.644
Yeah.
It's-it's really far but, um,

36:08.688 --> 36:11.865
the archeology programs thereare like the best in the world.

36:11.908 --> 36:13.432
-Yeah.
-And like the history there

36:13.475 --> 36:16.739
is just so awesome. So

36:19.351 --> 36:20.526
Very awesome.

36:20.569 --> 36:21.788
Hm-mm, thanks.

36:23.268 --> 36:24.530
Does your mom know?

36:25.792 --> 36:26.836
Kind of holding off on that.

36:26.880 --> 36:29.926
She's so attached.

36:29.970 --> 36:30.927
[John] Right.

36:30.971 --> 36:32.190
-Yeah.
-[John] Well

36:33.843 --> 36:35.018
Thank you. [giggles]

36:36.455 --> 36:38.892
Yeah, she wants me
to stay here,

36:38.935 --> 36:42.243
but the state programs
are so awful.

36:42.287 --> 36:43.505
Ahh!

36:43.549 --> 36:46.421
-[sudden splashing of water]
-[tense music]

36:50.469 --> 36:52.775
[crow cawing]

36:58.868 --> 37:02.132
[tense music building up]

37:02.176 --> 37:04.222
[breathes deeply]
I'm sorry.

37:05.571 --> 37:07.050
Are you kidding me?
I'm sorry!

37:08.095 --> 37:09.314
I didn't want youto ruin your dress.

37:09.357 --> 37:10.619
And I-I just reacted.

37:10.663 --> 37:11.838
I didn't really knowwhat to do.

37:13.187 --> 37:14.144
[Libby panting]

37:14.188 --> 37:17.931
Hey, hey, Libby, Libby.

37:17.974 --> 37:18.975
Listen

37:20.107 --> 37:21.935
it's okay!

37:21.978 --> 37:23.458
We're both scientists.

37:23.502 --> 37:24.459
Right?

37:24.503 --> 37:25.504
Hm-mm.

37:25.547 --> 37:27.680
This is totally normal.

37:27.723 --> 37:30.639
Look, it'sit's no big deal.

37:30.683 --> 37:33.686
[tense music]

37:38.865 --> 37:40.519
You have a little red
in your hair.

37:57.100 --> 38:00.103
[boat scrapes]

38:06.153 --> 38:07.720
[Libby breathing rapidly]

38:07.763 --> 38:09.852
Just chuck the shirt
in the trash.

38:09.896 --> 38:12.899
[shower running]

38:24.302 --> 38:25.477
[knock on door]

38:26.478 --> 38:28.044
[John] Hey, Libby?

38:28.088 --> 38:29.394
Are you okay?

38:29.437 --> 38:32.701
[water dripping from shower]

38:32.745 --> 38:34.312
[John continues to knock]

38:34.355 --> 38:35.748
Libby?

38:49.457 --> 38:50.850
-Hey, Libby?
-I'm in the shower.

38:50.893 --> 38:52.330
Thank you.

38:52.373 --> 38:53.983
Okay. Sorry.

38:55.550 --> 38:56.986
Just checking.

39:11.261 --> 39:12.350
[door closes]

39:18.138 --> 39:21.141
[dramatic music]

40:14.020 --> 40:17.371
[John inhales]

40:58.281 --> 40:59.935
[door squeaks open]

41:11.904 --> 41:13.383
[knocking on door]

41:16.212 --> 41:17.387
Mom?

41:19.825 --> 41:21.435
[knocks again]

41:23.916 --> 41:25.613
[doorknob rotates]

41:25.657 --> 41:29.878
[door hinges squeak]

41:31.576 --> 41:34.579
[tense music]

41:45.851 --> 41:48.854
[tense music building up]

42:19.928 --> 42:21.582
[Libby panting]

42:21.626 --> 42:24.585
[dry leaves rustling]

42:28.894 --> 42:31.897
[suspenseful music]

42:54.310 --> 42:57.313
[long beep,
disturbance in line]

43:05.974 --> 43:08.977
[long beep]

43:15.505 --> 43:16.637
[keys clacking softly]

43:47.102 --> 43:49.670
[laptop keys clacking]

43:59.637 --> 44:01.987
-[laptop keys clacking]
-[Libby breathes deeply]

44:14.564 --> 44:15.609
[soft knock on door]

44:21.746 --> 44:24.749
[door squeaks open]

44:47.423 --> 44:50.600
[door hinges squeak]

44:55.127 --> 44:58.130
[suspenseful music]

44:59.261 --> 45:00.480
Mm-mm.

45:00.523 --> 45:03.004
[exhales deeply]

45:53.185 --> 45:56.188
[suspenseful music
slowly building up]

46:30.875 --> 46:32.267
[floorboards creaking]

46:32.311 --> 46:33.834
Mom!

46:33.878 --> 46:35.053
[knocking on door]

46:35.096 --> 46:36.184
Mom!

46:37.969 --> 46:40.058
[rattles doorknob]

46:40.101 --> 46:41.102
Mom!

46:42.582 --> 46:44.845
Mom, John just, uh--

46:46.978 --> 46:47.935
-[banging on door]
-Mom?

46:47.979 --> 46:49.807
[breathing rapidly]

46:57.031 --> 46:59.642
[water lapping gently]

47:14.048 --> 47:17.051
[suspenseful music]

47:22.448 --> 47:24.319
[approaching footsteps]

47:24.363 --> 47:26.408
[water lapping gently]

47:26.452 --> 47:27.714
John?

47:27.757 --> 47:28.976
Libby?

47:32.327 --> 47:33.720
What are you doing out here?

47:35.853 --> 47:38.290
I don't know.
I just woke up out here.

47:38.333 --> 47:39.726
Ah, I saw you!

47:39.769 --> 47:41.684
I saw you walk into the lake!

47:41.728 --> 47:43.121
-What?
-Right here.

47:43.164 --> 47:45.906
I saw you walk into the Lake.Towards this like light!

47:47.516 --> 47:52.217
[scoffs]
I'm-I'm pretty dry.

47:52.260 --> 47:53.871
What?

47:55.742 --> 47:57.396
Libby, I should have
mentioned this earlier,

47:57.439 --> 47:58.832
and I'm really sorry.

48:00.921 --> 48:03.489
I suffer from somnambulism.

48:05.056 --> 48:06.318
It's sleepwalking.

48:07.754 --> 48:10.148
I'm really sorry
if I scared you.

48:13.934 --> 48:15.370
I feel like everything
that I have done

48:15.414 --> 48:18.243
since you got here has been
an absolute catastrophe!

48:21.159 --> 48:22.769
I have this way of

48:26.120 --> 48:28.166
I just fuck everything up.

48:29.515 --> 48:31.691
Except for my research.

48:34.128 --> 48:39.264
It's the one time
that I-I like I work.

48:40.787 --> 48:42.049
Does that make sense?

48:48.012 --> 48:49.100
Look, please,
come back inside.

48:49.143 --> 48:51.667
I got to keep
one of you healthy. I--

48:51.711 --> 48:53.060
[Libby breathes rapidly]

48:53.104 --> 48:54.366
[John exhales]

48:54.409 --> 48:56.672
Do you always lock the doorswhen you sleepwalk?

48:56.716 --> 48:59.719
[tense music]

49:11.644 --> 49:12.645
[Michelle] <i>Libby?</i>

49:14.212 --> 49:15.300
<i>Libbbyyyy!</i>

49:19.391 --> 49:20.827
<i>Libby!!!</i>

49:23.047 --> 49:24.004
Mom?

49:24.048 --> 49:25.832
[Michelle]
Libby, in here!

49:25.875 --> 49:27.486
[Libby] Mom?

49:27.529 --> 49:28.791
What's wrong?

49:28.835 --> 49:30.141
Libby[breathes deeply]

49:30.184 --> 49:32.752
I need you to take the car,and go into town,

49:32.795 --> 49:34.536
and get me medicine.Okay?

49:34.580 --> 49:38.801
Something calledcyclizine and Ginger Root.

49:38.845 --> 49:40.194
And whatever else.

49:40.238 --> 49:42.196
-Everything!
-Mom, I can't drive!

49:42.240 --> 49:44.372
If somebody pulls you over,tell 'em it's an emergency.

49:44.416 --> 49:46.418
Well then, we-we need to
call an ambulance!

49:46.461 --> 49:47.985
[Michelle][labored breathing] Oh, God.

49:49.508 --> 49:52.032
It's not really an emergency.

49:52.076 --> 49:54.034
-What?
-[Michelle] I

49:54.078 --> 49:55.644
Mom?

49:55.688 --> 49:57.864
I need you to also get mea pregnancy test.

49:59.735 --> 50:02.390
-[whispers] Mom!
-Libby! Go! Please!

50:02.434 --> 50:03.609
[Libby] Why can't John do it?

50:03.652 --> 50:05.611
Because John's onone of his marathon jogs.

